\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">to make somebody/something use all their effort, abilities, supplies, etc.</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Jim didn't really have to extend himself in the exam.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">Hospitals were already fully extended because of the epidemic.</span></li></ul>      </li> <span class=\"xrefs\" hclass=\"xrefs\" xt=\"see\" htag=\"span\" id=\"extend_xrgs_9\"><span class=\"prefix\">see also</span> <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/extension\" title=\"extension definition\"><span class=\"xr-g\" href=\"extension_e\" id=\"extend_xrg_11\" bord=\"n\"><span class=\"xh\">extension</span></span></a><span class=\"sep\">,</span> <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/extensive\" title=\"extensive definition\"><span class=\"xr-g\" id=\"extend_xrg_12\" bord=\"n\" href=\"extensive_e\"><span class=\"xh\">extensive</span></span></a></span></span><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"extend_unbox_7\" unbox=\"wordorigin\"><span class=\"box_title\">Word Origin</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">late Middle English: from Latin <span class=\"ei\">extendere</span> ‘stretch out’, from <span class=\"ei\">ex-</span> ‘out’ + <span class=\"ei\">tendere</span> ‘stretch’.</span></span></span></div></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/extend\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">extend</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/extend\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">extend</span></a> in the Oxford Le